Package: echolib0
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: A simple and efficient IPC library
 A simple and efficient interprocess communication (IPC) library for
 Linux written in C++11. The core part of the code was developed as a
 bachelor's thesis of Urban Å kvorc with the title `Development of a
 library for interprocess communication in interactive systems` in 2015
 at the University of Ljubljana, Faculty of Computer and Information
 Science. The library was later added some documentation and some polish
 and is now made available under MIT license.

Package: echolib-dev
Section: libdevel
Architecture: any
Depends: echolib0 (= ${binary:Version}), ${misc:Depends}
Description: A simple and efficient IPC library (development files)
 This package contains files needed to develop with echolib.

Package: echolib-daemon
Section: misc
Architecture: any
Depends: echolib0 (= ${binary:Version}), ${misc:Depends}
Description: Daemon for routing messages between clients using echolib IPC library
 This package contains the daemon for routing messages between clients
 written using echolib.

Package: python-echolib
Architecture: all
Multi-Arch: foreign
Section: python
Depends: ${misc:Depends},
         ${python:Depends},
         echolib0 (= ${binary:Version})
Description: echolib bindings for Python 2
 This package provides echolib bindings for Python 2.

